{"author":{"id":"138b13306404778af60b1d60d606624fec41556ddac480b2d5f762806ce84fed"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"LNLSktXvy8sULIpFygamqtKN5vg=","kind":"spec","title":"Design: auto-install for `kref completion`","content_type":"text/markdown"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782958625,"nonce":"W+ylyKLYIbra8o2PyjZpKaXJXLo=","body":"# Design: auto-install for `kref completion`\n\n**Date:** 2026-06-29\n**Status:** Approved (pending implementation plan)\n**Branch:** new branch off `main` (e.g. `feat/completion-auto-install`); the\ncurrent `feat/show-rendering-pager` branch is unrelated work.\n\n## Problem\n\n`kref` currently relies on cobra's built-in `completion` command, whose\nper-shell subcommands (`bash`/`zsh`/`fish`/`powershell`) only print a script to\nstdout. Users must know the correct redirect target for their shell and run it\nby hand. We want `kref completion \u003cshell\u003e --install` to write the script to the\nshell's standard completion directory automatically.\n\n## Goals\n\n- `kref completion bash|zsh|fish --install` writes the completion script to the\n  standard, auto-loaded location for that shell.\n- `--dir \u003cpath\u003e` overrides the target directory (the filename is still chosen by\n  shell). Primary use: zsh users whose `fpath` does not include our default dir.\n- Without `--install`, behavior is unchanged: the script is printed to stdout.\n- No edits to user dotfiles (`.bashrc`, `.zshrc`, `$PROFILE`). We write the\n  script file only, and *print* any follow-up step the user must take.\n- Honor the existing output contract: human text via `emit()`, `--json` returns\n  a structured result.\n- Preserve cobra parity: the `--no-descriptions` flag and the per-shell `Long`\n  help text are kept.\n\n## Non-goals\n\n- Editing rc files or `$PROFILE`.\n- An `install` subcommand with shell auto-detection (rejected in favor of the\n  per-shell `--install` flag).\n- Uninstall. Re-running with a removed file is the user's responsibility; the\n  manual `rm \u003cpath\u003e` is trivial and out of scope.\n\n## Architecture\n\nCobra auto-generates the `completion` command and exposes no supported hook to\nadd a flag to its generated subcommands. We therefore:\n\n1. Disable the default command: `root.CompletionOptions.DisableDefaultCmd = true`\n   in `newRootCmd()` (`cmd/kref/main.go`).\n2. Add a custom `completion` parent command and four shell subcommands in a new\n   file `cmd/kref/completion.go`, registered into the existing `additional`\n   group (replacing the current `SetCompletionCommandGroupID(\"additional\")`\n   call, which no longer applies once the default command is gone).\n\nDisabling `DisableDefaultCmd` removes only the user-facing `completion` command.\nThe hidden `__complete` command that powers *dynamic* completion is unaffected,\nso tab-completion of args/flags keeps working.\n\nThe subcommands generate scripts with the cobra APIs verified in the module\ncache (`github.com/spf13/cobra@v1.10.2`):\n\n| Shell      | Generator (writer form)                    | `--install` | Install path (default)                                            |\n|------------|--------------------------------------------|-------------|-------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| bash       | `Root().GenBashCompletionV2(w, !noDesc)`   | yes         | `${XDG_DATA_HOME:-~/.local/share}/bash-completion/completions/kref` |\n| zsh        | `Root().GenZshCompletion(w)` / `…NoDesc`   | yes         | `${XDG_DATA_HOME:-~/.local/share}/zsh/site-functions/_kref`        |\n| fish       | `Root().GenFishCompletion(w, !noDesc)`     | yes         | `${XDG_CONFIG_HOME:-~/.config}/fish/completions/kref.fish`         |\n| powershell | `Root().GenPowerShellCompletionWithDesc(w)`| **no**      | n/a — print only                                                  |\n\nSubcommands reach the root via `cmd.Root()`, so no explicit root reference is\nthreaded through.\n\n### Why powershell has no `--install`\n\nPowerShell has no auto-loaded completion directory; the script must be added to\n`$PROFILE`. That conflicts with the \"no rc edits\" decision, and shipping an\n`--install` flag that cannot honor its contract violates the project's\n\"implement completely or not at all\" rule. The powershell subcommand stays\nprint-only and unchanged; its `Long` help explains the manual `$PROFILE` step\n(mirroring cobra's default text).\n\n## Behavior of `--install`\n\n1. Resolve the target file path (see \"Path resolution\" below).\n2. `os.MkdirAll(dir, 0o755)` the parent directory.\n3. Generate the script into the file (`0o644`), overwriting if present. Writing\n   is naturally idempotent — a second run produces the identical file.\n4. Emit the result:\n   - Human: `Installed completion to \u003cpath\u003e`. For **zsh only**, also print a\n     follow-up line telling the user to ensure the directory is in `fpath`\n     (we cannot read zsh's `fpath` from a Go process, so we instruct rather\n     than guess), e.g.:\n     ```\n     Installed completion to ~/.local/share/zsh/site-functions/_kref\n     Ensure this directory is in your fpath, then run: compinit\n       fpath=(~/.local/share/zsh/site-functions $fpath)   # add to ~/.zshrc if missing\n     ```\n   - JSON (`--json`): `{\"shell\":\"zsh\",\"path\":\"\u003cabs path\u003e\",\"installed\":true}`.\n\nGeneration/write errors are returned from `RunE` and surfaced by the existing\n`main()` error formatter; no error is swallowed.\n\n`--install` and `--dir` interact as follows:\n- `--dir` without `--install` is a usage error (`--dir requires --install`).\n- `--install` without `--dir` uses the per-shell default directory.\n- `--dir` is tilde-expanded (`~` → `$HOME`) and may be relative (resolved\n  against the process working directory). The shell-specific basename\n  (`kref`, `_kref`, `kref.fish`) is appended by us, not the user.\n\n## Path resolution (the testable seam)\n\nA pure function does all path logic with no I/O, reading environment through an\ninjected lookup so tests need no real env mutation:\n\n```go\n// completionInstallPath returns the absolute file path to install the\n// completion script for shell, honoring an optional dirOverride.\n// getenv is the environment lookup (os.Getenv in production).\nfunc completionInstallPath(shell, dirOverride string, getenv func(string) string) (string, error)\n```\n\n- `shell` ∈ {bash, zsh, fish}. `powershell` / unknown → error (powershell never\n  reaches here because it has no `--install`).\n- XDG resolution: use `$XDG_DATA_HOME` / `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME` when non-empty,\n  else fall back to `$HOME/.local/share` / `$HOME/.config`.\n- Empty `$HOME` with no override and no XDG var set → error (cannot resolve a\n  default location).\n- `dirOverride` non-empty → `filepath.Join(expand(dirOverride), basename(shell))`.\n\nFilename per shell: bash → `kref`, zsh → `_kref`, fish → `kref.fish`.\n\n## Files touched\n\n- `cmd/kref/main.go` — set `CompletionOptions.DisableDefaultCmd = true`; register\n  the custom `completion` command into the `additional` group; drop the now-moot\n  `SetCompletionCommandGroupID` call.\n- `cmd/kref/completion.go` — **new**. `newCompletionCmd()`, the four shell\n  subcommands, `completionInstallPath`, and a small shared install helper.\n- `cmd/kref/completion_test.go` — **new**. Ginkgo suite (see Testing).\n- Docs: update README / CLI docs where completion setup is described.\n\n## Testing\n\nFramework: Ginkgo v2 + Gomega, run via `task test` (wires `KREF_GITLEAKS`).\n\nUnit (pure, no filesystem):\n- `completionInstallPath` table over {bash, zsh, fish} × {XDG set, XDG unset\n  with HOME, override dir, relative override, tilde override}.\n- Error cases: unknown shell; empty HOME with no XDG and no override.\n\nCommand-level (temp dir via Ginkgo, `--dir` pointed at it):\n- `completion bash --install --dir \u003ctmp\u003e` writes `\u003ctmp\u003e/kref`, file is\n  non-empty and parseable as the same content `completion bash` prints.\n- zsh writes `_kref` and the human output includes the fpath follow-up line.\n- fish writes `kref.fish`.\n- Idempotency: running twice yields byte-identical files.\n- `--json` returns `{\"shell\",\"path\",\"installed\":true}` with an absolute path.\n- `--dir` without `--install` → usage error.\n- `powershell` has no `--install` flag (flag lookup returns nil) and still\n  prints a script.\n- Parity: `--no-descriptions` is accepted by bash/zsh/fish.\n- Regression: dynamic completion still works — `kref __complete \u003cprefix\u003e`\n  returns expected candidates (guards against the `DisableDefaultCmd` change).\n- Help completeness: the existing `cli_test.go` walker skips `completion`; the\n  new subcommands are non-leaf/known and should not break it — verify the suite\n  stays green (add the subcommand names to the skip set if needed).\n\n## Risks / tradeoffs\n\n- **zsh fpath**: our default dir is not guaranteed to be in the user's `fpath`.\n  Mitigation: printed instruction + `--dir` override. We deliberately do not\n  edit `.zshrc`.\n- **Replacing cobra's default command**: small maintenance cost — if cobra\n  changes its default help text we won't inherit it. Mitigation: our `Long`\n  text is copied from cobra v1.10.2 and is stable; the `__complete` regression\n  test guards the dynamic-completion path."}]}